P_HTM[2843]="*“Chadvārārammaṇesvettha,* **";
P_HTM[2844]="*viññāṇesu ca phassesu;* **";
P_HTM[2845]="*Vedanāsu ca dvārassa,* **";
P_HTM[2846]="*suttā honti visuṃ aṭṭha.* **";
P_HTM[2847]="*Saññā sañcetanā taṇhā,* **";
P_HTM[2848]="*vitakkesu vicāre ca;* **";
P_HTM[2849]="*Gocarassa visuṃ aṭṭha,* **";
P_HTM[2850]="*pañcakkhandhe ca pacceke.* **";
P_HTM[2851]="*Soḷasasvettha mūlesu,* **";
P_HTM[2852]="*aniccaṃ dukkhamanattā;* **";
P_HTM[2853]="*Khayā vayā virāgā ca,* **";
P_HTM[2854]="*nirodhā paṭinissaggā.* **";
P_HTM[2855]="*Kamaṃ aṭṭhānupassanā,* **";
P_HTM[2856]="*yojetvāna visuṃ visuṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2857]="*Sampiṇḍitesu sabbesu,* **";
P_HTM[2858]="*honti pañca satāni ca;* **";
P_HTM[2859]="*Aṭṭhavīsati suttāni,* **";
P_HTM[2860]="*āhuneyye ca vaggike”.* **";
P_HTM[2861]="*Āhuneyyavaggo dasamo.* **";
P_HTM[2862]="*111. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**615*";
P_HTM[2863]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya satta dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“Mendicants, for insight into greed, seven things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[2864]="*Katame satta?**What seven?*";
P_HTM[2865]="*Satisambojjhaṅgo … pe …**The awakening factor of mindfulness …*";
P_HTM[2866]="*upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo—**the awakening factor of equanimity.*";
P_HTM[2867]="*rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime satta dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**These seven things should be developed for insight into greed.”*";
P_HTM[2868]="*111. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**616*";
P_HTM[2869]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya satta dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“Mendicants, for insight into greed, seven things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[2870]="*Katame satta?**What seven?*";
P_HTM[2871]="*Aniccasaññā, anattasaññā, asubhasaññā, ādīnavasaññā, pahānasaññā, virāgasaññā, nirodhasaññā—**The perception of impermanence, the perception of not-self, the perception of ugliness, the perception of drawbacks, the perception of giving up, the perception of fading away, and the perception of cessation.*";
P_HTM[2872]="*rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime satta dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**These seven things should be developed for insight into greed.”*";
P_HTM[2873]="*111. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**617*";
P_HTM[2874]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya satta dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“Mendicants, for insight into greed, seven things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[2875]="*Katame satta?**What seven?*";
P_HTM[2876]="*Asubhasaññā, maraṇasaññā, āhāre paṭikūlasaññā, sabbaloke anabhiratasaññā, aniccasaññā, anicce dukkhasaññā, dukkhe anattasaññā—**The perceptions of ugliness, death, repulsiveness of food, dissatisfaction with the whole world, impermanence, suffering in impermanence, and not-self in suffering.*";
P_HTM[2877]="*rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime satta dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**These seven things should be developed for insight into greed.”*";
